cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you reference LocalGhost in academic or published work, please cite it using the metadata below."
type: software
title: "LocalGhost"
abstract: >-
  LocalGhost is a local-first, privacy-focused AI platform built on cypherpunk
  principles. All inference and data storage runs on user-owned hardware with
  no cloud dependency. Fully open-source. The architecture consists of six
  daemons (Scribe, Observer, Auditor, Weaver, Sentinel, Shadow) that each
  handle one function, communicating over local Unix sockets. The project
  includes a hidden-volume and duress-PIN security model designed to protect
  against compelled access, and a planned peer-to-peer backup layer (The Mist)
  using Reed-Solomon erasure coding. The project is currently in Phase 0
  (website and architecture documented, first commits pending).
